Lucille Ball, the leggy showgirl, model and B-grade movie queen whose pumpkin

Of course, the block broke.
Born to an electrician father and pianist mother on Aug. 6, 1911, in a suburb of Jamestown, N.Y., Miss Ball had set her sights on stardom almost from the first.
She later told an interviewer, "It was, at least for me, true love from the start."
In place of Desilu, Miss Ball, along with Morton, launched the much smaller Lucille Ball Productions Inc. and in 1968, began filming "Here's Lucy," a series featuring Desi Jr. and Lucie.
With her children's careers off the launching pad, the comedienne, then 63, decided it was time to retire her legendary character.
